{"documentCount":26,"nextId":26,"documentIds":{"0":"pages/docs.mdx#intro","1":"pages/docs.mdx#purpose","2":"pages/docs.mdx#cofhesdk-entrypoints","3":"pages/docs.mdx#import-examples","4":"pages/example.mdx#example","5":"pages/getting-started.mdx#get-started","6":"pages/#hello-world","7":"pages/docs/client.mdx#client","8":"pages/docs/client.mdx#1-create-a-config","9":"pages/docs/client.mdx#2-create-a-client","10":"pages/docs/client.mdx#3-create-viem-clients-adapters","11":"pages/docs/client.mdx#ethers-v6-adapter","12":"pages/docs/client.mdx#ethers-v5-adapter","13":"pages/docs/client.mdx#wagmi-adapter","14":"pages/docs/client.mdx#4-connect","15":"pages/docs/client.mdx#reconnect-behavior","16":"pages/docs/client.mdx#5-disconnect","17":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#migrating-from-cofhejs","18":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#key-changes","19":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#requirements","20":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#installation","21":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#migration","22":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#initializing-the-library","23":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#encrypting-inputs","24":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#decrypting-handles","25":"pages/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs.mdx#permits"},"fieldIds":{"title":0,"titles":1,"text":2},"fieldLength":{"0":[1,1,1],"1":[1,1,50],"2":[4,1,76],"3":[2,4,13],"4":[1,1,6],"5":[2,1,3],"6":[3,1,9],"7":[1,1,26],"8":[4,1,43],"9":[4,1,16],"10":[6,1,43],"11":[3,7,20],"12":[3,7,20],"13":[2,7,28],"14":[2,1,31],"15":[2,3,17],"16":[2,1,36],"17":[3,1,17],"18":[3,4,51],"19":[2,4,10],"20":[2,4,5],"21":[1,4,1],"22":[3,4,37],"23":[2,4,18],"24":[2,4,15],"25":[1,4,39]},"averageFieldLength":[2.3846153846153846,2.8076923076923075,24.26923076923077],"storedFields":{"0":{"href":"/docs#intro","html":"</header>\n","isPage":true,"text":"\n","title":"Intro","titles":[]},"1":{"href":"/docs#purpose","html":"\n<p><code>@cofhe/sdk</code> is the core library for integrating with Fhenix’s CoFHE coprocessor.</p>\n<p>It provides:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A typed client for encrypting inputs and decrypting handles.</li>\n<li>Key fetching + key storage abstractions (with sensible defaults per runtime).</li>\n<li>Permit utilities (create/validate/store/serialize) for decryption authorization.</li>\n<li>Optional helpers for chain definitions and popular wallet/provider stacks.</li>\n</ul>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\n@cofhe/sdk is the core library for integrating with Fhenix’s CoFHE coprocessor.\nIt provides:\n\nA typed client for encrypting inputs and decrypting handles.\nKey fetching + key storage abstractions (with sensible defaults per runtime).\nPermit utilities (create/validate/store/serialize) for decryption authorization.\nOptional helpers for chain definitions and popular wallet/provider stacks.\n\n","title":"Purpose","titles":["Intro"]},"2":{"href":"/docs#cofhesdk-entrypoints","html":"\n<p>The SDK ships multiple entrypoints so you can pick the right defaults for your runtime.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>@cofhe/sdk</code> (core)\n<ul>\n<li>Environment-agnostic exports: core client/config factories, types, and shared utilities.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><code>@cofhe/sdk/web</code>\n<ul>\n<li>Browser defaults: IndexedDB-based key storage, TFHE-WASM initialization, and optional Web Worker proof generation.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><code>@cofhe/sdk/node</code>\n<ul>\n<li>Node.js defaults: filesystem-based key storage and <code>node-tfhe</code> initialization.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><code>@cofhe/sdk/permits</code>\n<ul>\n<li>Permit utilities: create/validate/serialize permits, permit storage helpers, and sealing utilities.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><code>@cofhe/sdk/adapters</code>\n<ul>\n<li>Adapter layer: helpers for integrating with <code>ethers</code> (v5/v6), Wagmi, and Hardhat signers.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><code>@cofhe/sdk/chains</code>\n<ul>\n<li>Chain definitions + helpers: built-in supported chains and <code>getChainById</code> / <code>getChainByName</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\nThe SDK ships multiple entrypoints so you can pick the right defaults for your runtime.\n\n@cofhe/sdk (core)\n\nEnvironment-agnostic exports: core client/config factories, types, and shared utilities.\n\n\n@cofhe/sdk/web\n\nBrowser defaults: IndexedDB-based key storage, TFHE-WASM initialization, and optional Web Worker proof generation.\n\n\n@cofhe/sdk/node\n\nNode.js defaults: filesystem-based key storage and node-tfhe initialization.\n\n\n@cofhe/sdk/permits\n\nPermit utilities: create/validate/serialize permits, permit storage helpers, and sealing utilities.\n\n\n@cofhe/sdk/adapters\n\nAdapter layer: helpers for integrating with ethers (v5/v6), Wagmi, and Hardhat signers.\n\n\n@cofhe/sdk/chains\n\nChain definitions + helpers: built-in supported chains and getChainById / getChainByName.\n\n\n\n","title":"@cofhe/sdk entrypoints","titles":["Intro"]},"3":{"href":"/docs#import-examples","html":"\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// @noErrors</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// or</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">  createCofhesdkClient </span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">as</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> createCofhesdkClientNode</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">  createCofhesdkConfig </span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">as</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> createCofhesdkConfigNode</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">} from </span><span style=\"color:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#96D0FF\">&#x27;@cofhe/sdk/node&#x27;</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span></code></pre>","isPage":false,"text":"\n// @noErrors\n \n// or\n \n  createCofhesdkClient as createCofhesdkClientNode,\n  createCofhesdkConfig as createCofhesdkConfigNode,\n} from &#x27;@cofhe/sdk/node&#x27;;\n \n \n ","title":"Import examples","titles":["Intro","@cofhe/sdk entrypoints"]},"4":{"href":"/example#example","html":"</header>\n<p>This is an example page.</p>","isPage":true,"text":"\nThis is an example page.","title":"Example","titles":[]},"5":{"href":"/getting-started#get-started","html":"</header>\n<p>Hello world!</p>","isPage":true,"text":"\nHello world!","title":"Get started","titles":[]},"6":{"href":"#hello-world","html":"<div role=\"doc-subtitle\">This is my first page</div></header>\n<p>Welcome to my docs.</p>","isPage":true,"text":"This is my first page\nWelcome to my docs.","title":"Hello, World!","titles":[]},"7":{"href":"/docs/client#client","html":"</header>\n<p>This page covers the core SDK lifecycle:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a config (<code>createCofhesdkConfig</code>)</li>\n<li>Create a client (<code>createCofhesdkClient</code>)</li>\n<li>Create viem clients (either directly, or via <code>@cofhe/sdk/adapters</code>)</li>\n<li>Connect + disconnect</li>\n</ol>\n","isPage":true,"text":"\nThis page covers the core SDK lifecycle:\n\nCreate a config (createCofhesdkConfig)\nCreate a client (createCofhesdkClient)\nCreate viem clients (either directly, or via @cofhe/sdk/adapters)\nConnect + disconnect\n\n","title":"Client","titles":[]},"8":{"href":"/docs/client#1-create-a-config","html":"\n<p>Pick the entrypoint that matches your runtime:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Browser apps: <code>@cofhe/sdk/web</code></li>\n<li>Node.js scripts/backends: <code>@cofhe/sdk/node</code></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The only required field is <code>supportedChains</code>.</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// @noErrors</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> config</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> =</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\"> createCofhesdkConfig</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">({</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">  supportedChains: [chains.sepolia],</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">  // Optional tweaks</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">  // permitGeneration: &#x27;ON_CONNECT&#x27;,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">  // defaultPermitExpiration: 60 * 60 * 24 * 30,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">  // useWorkers: true,</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">});</span></span></code></pre>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\nPick the entrypoint that matches your runtime:\n\nBrowser apps: @cofhe/sdk/web\nNode.js scripts/backends: @cofhe/sdk/node\n\nThe only required field is supportedChains.\n// @noErrors\n \n \n \nconst config = createCofhesdkConfig({\n  supportedChains: [chains.sepolia],\n \n  // Optional tweaks\n  // permitGeneration: &#x27;ON_CONNECT&#x27;,\n  // defaultPermitExpiration: 60 * 60 * 24 * 30,\n  // useWorkers: true,\n});\n","title":"1) Create a config","titles":["Client"]},"9":{"href":"/docs/client#2-create-a-client","html":"\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// @noErrors</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// config from the previous step</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> config</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> CofhesdkConfig</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> cofhesdk</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> =</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\"> createCofhesdkClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">(config);</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">cofhesdk.connected; </span><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// false</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">cofhesdk.connecting; </span><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// false</span></span></code></pre>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\n// @noErrors\n \n \n \n// config from the previous step\ndeclare const config: CofhesdkConfig;\n \nconst cofhesdk = createCofhesdkClient(config);\n \ncofhesdk.connected; // false\ncofhesdk.connecting; // false\n","title":"2) Create a client","titles":["Client"]},"10":{"href":"/docs/client#3-create-viem-clients-adapters","html":"\n<p>The SDK connects to CoFHE using viem clients:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code>PublicClient</code>: read-only chain access</li>\n<li><code>WalletClient</code>: signing + sending transactions</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you already have viem clients, you can pass them directly to <code>cofhesdk.connect(publicClient, walletClient)</code>.</p>\n<p>If you’re using another wallet/provider stack, <code>@cofhe/sdk/adapters</code> can convert it into viem-shaped clients.</p>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\nThe SDK connects to CoFHE using viem clients:\n\nPublicClient: read-only chain access\nWalletClient: signing + sending transactions\n\nIf you already have viem clients, you can pass them directly to cofhesdk.connect(publicClient, walletClient).\nIf you’re using another wallet/provider stack, @cofhe/sdk/adapters can convert it into viem-shaped clients.\n","title":"3) Create viem clients (adapters)","titles":["Client"]},"11":{"href":"/docs/client#ethers-v6-adapter","html":"\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// @noErrors</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// Your ethers instances</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> provider</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> Parameters</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">typeof</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> Ethers6Adapter&gt;[</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\">0</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">];</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> signer</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> Parameters</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">typeof</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> Ethers6Adapter&gt;[</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\">1</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">];</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> { </span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\">publicClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\">walletClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> } </span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> await</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\"> Ethers6Adapter</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">(provider, signer);</span></span></code></pre>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\n// @noErrors\n \n \n// Your ethers instances\ndeclare const provider: Parameters&lt;typeof Ethers6Adapter&gt;[0];\ndeclare const signer: Parameters&lt;typeof Ethers6Adapter&gt;[1];\n \nconst { publicClient, walletClient } = await Ethers6Adapter(provider, signer);\n","title":"Ethers v6 adapter","titles":["Client","3) Create viem clients (adapters)"]},"12":{"href":"/docs/client#ethers-v5-adapter","html":"\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// @noErrors</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// Your ethers instances</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> provider</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> Parameters</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">typeof</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> Ethers5Adapter&gt;[</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\">0</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">];</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> signer</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> Parameters</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">&lt;</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">typeof</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> Ethers5Adapter&gt;[</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\">1</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">];</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> { </span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\">publicClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">, </span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\">walletClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> } </span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">=</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> await</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\"> Ethers5Adapter</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">(provider, signer);</span></span></code></pre>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\n// @noErrors\n \n \n// Your ethers instances\ndeclare const provider: Parameters&lt;typeof Ethers5Adapter&gt;[0];\ndeclare const signer: Parameters&lt;typeof Ethers5Adapter&gt;[1];\n \nconst { publicClient, walletClient } = await Ethers5Adapter(provider, signer);\n","title":"Ethers v5 adapter","titles":["Client","3) Create viem clients (adapters)"]},"13":{"href":"/docs/client#wagmi-adapter","html":"\n<p>If you’re using Wagmi, you already have viem clients; the adapter just validates and passes them through.</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// @noErrors</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> publicClient</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> PublicClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> walletClient</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> WalletClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> clients</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> =</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> await</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\"> WagmiAdapter</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">(walletClient, publicClient);</span></span></code></pre>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\nIf you’re using Wagmi, you already have viem clients; the adapter just validates and passes them through.\n// @noErrors\n \n \n \ndeclare const publicClient: PublicClient;\ndeclare const walletClient: WalletClient;\n \nconst clients = await WagmiAdapter(walletClient, publicClient);\n","title":"Wagmi adapter","titles":["Client","3) Create viem clients (adapters)"]},"14":{"href":"/docs/client#4-connect","html":"\n<p>Connecting initializes the SDK’s in-memory connection state (<code>account</code>, <code>chainId</code>, and the viem clients).</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// @noErrors</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> config</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> CofhesdkConfig</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> publicClient</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> PublicClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> walletClient</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\"> WalletClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">;</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> cofhesdk</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> =</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\"> createCofhesdkClient</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">(config);</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">await</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> cofhesdk.</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\">connect</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">(publicClient, walletClient);</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">cofhesdk.connected; </span><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// true</span></span></code></pre>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\nConnecting initializes the SDK’s in-memory connection state (account, chainId, and the viem clients).\n// @noErrors\n \n \n \n \ndeclare const config: CofhesdkConfig;\ndeclare const publicClient: PublicClient;\ndeclare const walletClient: WalletClient;\n \nconst cofhesdk = createCofhesdkClient(config);\n \nawait cofhesdk.connect(publicClient, walletClient);\n \ncofhesdk.connected; // true\n","title":"4) Connect","titles":["Client"]},"15":{"href":"/docs/client#reconnect-behavior","html":"\n<p>Calling <code>connect</code> again with the same clients is a no-op. Calling it with new clients replaces the connection state.</p>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\nCalling connect again with the same clients is a no-op. Calling it with new clients replaces the connection state.\n","title":"Reconnect behavior","titles":["Client","4) Connect"]},"16":{"href":"/docs/client#5-disconnect","html":"\n<p>Disconnect clears only the in-memory connection state (clients/account/chainId) and marks the client as disconnected.</p>\n<p>It does <strong>not</strong> delete persisted permits or stored FHE keys.</p>\n<pre class=\"shiki shiki-themes github-light github-dark-dimmed\" style=\"background-color:#fff;--shiki-dark-bg:#22272e;color:#24292e;--shiki-dark:#adbac7\" tabindex=\"0\"><code><span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// @noErrors</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">declare</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\"> const</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> cofhesdk</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> { </span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\">disconnect</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">()</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> void</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">; </span><span style=\"color:#E36209;--shiki-dark:#F69D50\">connected</span><span style=\"color:#D73A49;--shiki-dark:#F47067\">:</span><span style=\"color:#005CC5;--shiki-dark:#6CB6FF\"> boolean</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\"> };</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">cofhesdk.</span><span style=\"color:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#DCBDFB\">disconnect</span><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">();</span></span>\n<span class=\"line\" data-empty-line=\"true\"> </span>\n<span class=\"line\"><span style=\"color:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#ADBAC7\">cofhesdk.connected; </span><span style=\"color:#6A737D;--shiki-dark:#768390\">// false</span></span></code></pre>","isPage":false,"text":"\nDisconnect clears only the in-memory connection state (clients/account/chainId) and marks the client as disconnected.\nIt does not delete persisted permits or stored FHE keys.\n// @noErrors\ndeclare const cofhesdk: { disconnect(): void; connected: boolean };\n \ncofhesdk.disconnect();\n \ncofhesdk.connected; // false","title":"5) Disconnect","titles":["Client"]},"17":{"href":"/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs#migrating-from-cofhejs","html":"</header>\n<p><code>cofhesdk</code> is an improved replacement for <code>cofhejs</code>. Improvements are focused around:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>explicit api</li>\n<li>developer experience</li>\n<li>flexibility</li>\n</ul>\n","isPage":true,"text":"\ncofhesdk is an improved replacement for cofhejs. Improvements are focused around:\n\nexplicit api\ndeveloper experience\nflexibility\n\n","title":"Migrating from cofhejs","titles":[]},"18":{"href":"/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs#key-changes","html":"\n<ul>\n<li>Functions are encapsulated in a new <code>client</code> class.</li>\n<li>No longer need to wait for initialization (keys fetched during encrypt)</li>\n<li>Permits must be explicitly generated, preventing unknown signature requests in users&#x27; wallets.</li>\n<li>Top level configuration of cofhesdk behavior.</li>\n<li>Explicit overrides and settings in <code>encryptInputs</code> and <code>decryptHandle</code> functions.</li>\n<li>Better feedback and error handling in functions.</li>\n<li>Better multichain usage</li>\n</ul>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\n\nFunctions are encapsulated in a new client class.\nNo longer need to wait for initialization (keys fetched during encrypt)\nPermits must be explicitly generated, preventing unknown signature requests in users&#x27; wallets.\nTop level configuration of cofhesdk behavior.\nExplicit overrides and settings in encryptInputs and decryptHandle functions.\nBetter feedback and error handling in functions.\nBetter multichain usage\n\n","title":"Key Changes:","titles":["Migrating from cofhejs",null]},"19":{"href":"/docs/migrating-from-cofhejs#requirements","html":"\n<ul>\n<li>Node.js: 18+</li>\n<li>React: 18+</li>\n<li>TypeScript: 5+</li>\n<li>Wagmi: 2+</li>\n<li>Viem: 2+</li>\n</ul>\n","isPage":false,"text":"\n\nNode.js: 18+\nReact: 18+\nTypeScript: 5+\